StorageLensConfiguration.StorageLensArn.description: This property contains the details of the ARN of the S3 Storage Lens configuration. This property is read-only.

ActivityMetrics.description: This property contains the details of account-level activity metrics for S3 Storage Lens.

AdvancedCostOptimizationMetrics.description: This property contains the details of account-level advanced cost optimization metrics for S3 Storage Lens.

AdvancedDataProtectionMetrics.description: This property contains the details of account-level advanced data protection metrics for S3 Storage Lens.

BucketLevel.description: This property contains the details of the account-level bucket-level configurations for Amazon S3 Storage Lens. To enable bucket-level configurations, make sure to also set the same metrics at the account level.

DetailedStatusCodesMetrics.description: This property contains the details of account-level detailed status code metrics for S3 Storage Lens.

StorageLensGroupLevel.description: This property determines the scope of Storage Lens group data that is displayed in the Storage Lens dashboard.

AccountLevel.description: This resource contains the details of the account-level metrics for Amazon S3 Storage Lens.

IsEnabled.description: A property that indicates whether the activity metrics is enabled.

ActivityMetrics.description:
This resource enables Amazon S3 Storage Lens activity metrics. Activity metrics show details about how your storage is requested, such as requests (for example, All requests, Get requests, Put requests), bytes uploaded or downloaded, and errors.

For more information, see [Assessing your storage activity and usage with S3 Storage Lens](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/userguide/storage_lens.html) in the *Amazon S3 User Guide* . For a complete list of metrics, see [S3 Storage Lens metrics glossary](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/userguide/storage_lens_metrics_glossary.html) in the *Amazon S3 User Guide* .

IsEnabled.description: Indicates whether advanced cost optimization metrics are enabled.

AdvancedCostOptimizationMetrics.description:
This resource enables Amazon S3 Storage Lens advanced cost optimization metrics. Advanced cost optimization metrics provide insights that you can use to manage and optimize your storage costs, for example, lifecycle rule counts for transitions, expirations, and incomplete multipart uploads.

For more information, see [Assessing your storage activity and usage with S3 Storage Lens](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/userguide/storage_lens.html) in the *Amazon S3 User Guide* . For a complete list of metrics, see [S3 Storage Lens metrics glossary](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/userguide/storage_lens_metrics_glossary.html) in the *Amazon S3 User Guide* .

IsEnabled.description: Indicates whether advanced data protection metrics are enabled.

AdvancedDataProtectionMetrics.description:
This resource enables Amazon S3 Storage Lens advanced data protection metrics. Advanced data protection metrics provide insights that you can use to perform audits and protect your data, for example replication rule counts within and across Regions.

For more information, see [Assessing your storage activity and usage with S3 Storage Lens](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/userguide/storage_lens.html) in the *Amazon S3 User Guide* . For a complete list of metrics, see [S3 Storage Lens metrics glossary](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/userguide/storage_lens_metrics_glossary.html) in the *Amazon S3 User Guide* .

IsEnabled.description: Specifies whether the Advanced Performance Metrics is enabled or disabled.

Arn.description: This resource contains the ARN of the AWS Organization.

AwsOrg.description: This resource contains the details of the AWS Organization for Amazon S3 Storage Lens.

ActivityMetrics.description: A property for bucket-level activity metrics for S3 Storage Lens.

AdvancedCostOptimizationMetrics.description: A property for bucket-level advanced cost optimization metrics for S3 Storage Lens.

AdvancedDataProtectionMetrics.description: A property for bucket-level advanced data protection metrics for S3 Storage Lens.

DetailedStatusCodesMetrics.description: A property for bucket-level detailed status code metrics for S3 Storage Lens.

PrefixLevel.description: A property for bucket-level prefix-level storage metrics for S3 Storage Lens.

BucketLevel.description: A property for the bucket-level storage metrics for Amazon S3 Storage Lens.

Buckets.description: This property contains the details of the buckets for the Amazon S3 Storage Lens configuration. This should be the bucket Amazon Resource Name(ARN). For valid values, see [Buckets ARN format here](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/API/API_control_Include.html#API_control_Include_Contents) in the *Amazon S3 API Reference* .

Regions.description: This property contains the details of the Regions for the S3 Storage Lens configuration.

BucketsAndRegions.description: This resource contains the details of the buckets and Regions for the Amazon S3 Storage Lens configuration.

IsEnabled.description: This property identifies whether the CloudWatch publishing option for S3 Storage Lens is enabled.

CloudWatchMetrics.description:
This resource enables the Amazon CloudWatch publishing option for Amazon S3 Storage Lens metrics.

For more information, see [Monitor S3 Storage Lens metrics in CloudWatch](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/userguide/storage_lens_view_metrics_cloudwatch.html) in the *Amazon S3 User Guide* .
This property enables the Amazon CloudWatch publishing option for S3 Storage Lens metrics.

S3BucketDestination.description: This property contains the details of the bucket where the S3 Storage Lens metrics export will be placed.

StorageLensTableDestination.description: S3 Tables destination settings for the Amazon S3 Storage Lens metrics export.

DataExport.description: This resource contains the details of the Amazon S3 Storage Lens metrics export.

IsEnabled.description: Indicates whether detailed status code metrics are enabled.

DetailedStatusCodesMetrics.description:
This resource enables Amazon S3 Storage Lens detailed status code metrics. Detailed status code metrics generate metrics for HTTP status codes, such as `200 OK` , `403 Forbidden` , `503 Service Unavailable` and others.

For more information, see [Assessing your storage activity and usage with S3 Storage Lens](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/userguide/storage_lens.html) in the *Amazon S3 User Guide* . For a complete list of metrics, see [S3 Storage Lens metrics glossary](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/userguide/storage_lens_metrics_glossary.html) in the *Amazon S3 User Guide* .

Encryption.description: This resource contains the type of server-side encryption used to encrypt an Amazon S3 Storage Lens metrics export. For valid values, see the [StorageLensDataExportEncryption](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/API/API_control_StorageLensDataExportEncryption.html) in the *Amazon S3 API Reference* .

StorageMetrics.description: A property for the prefix-level storage metrics for Amazon S3 Storage Lens.

PrefixLevel.description: This resource contains the details of the prefix-level of the Amazon S3 Storage Lens.

IsEnabled.description: This property identifies whether the details of the prefix-level storage metrics for S3 Storage Lens are enabled.

SelectionCriteria.description: This property identifies whether the details of the prefix-level storage metrics for S3 Storage Lens are enabled.

PrefixLevelStorageMetrics.description: This resource contains the details of the prefix-level storage metrics for Amazon S3 Storage Lens.

AccountId.description: This property contains the details of the AWS account ID of the S3 Storage Lens export bucket destination.

Arn.description: This property contains the details of the ARN of the bucket destination of the S3 Storage Lens export.

Encryption.description: This property contains the details of the encryption of the bucket destination of the Amazon S3 Storage Lens metrics export.

Format.description: This property contains the details of the format of the S3 Storage Lens export bucket destination.

OutputSchemaVersion.description: This property contains the details of the output schema version of the S3 Storage Lens export bucket destination.

Prefix.description: This property contains the details of the prefix of the bucket destination of the S3 Storage Lens export .

S3BucketDestination.description: This resource contains the details of the bucket where the Amazon S3 Storage Lens metrics export will be placed.

KeyId.description: Specifies the Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the customer managed AWS  key to use for encrypting the S3 Storage Lens metrics export file. Amazon S3 only supports symmetric encryption keys. For more information, see [Special-purpose keys](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/kms/latest/developerguide/key-types.html) in the *AWS Key Management Service Developer Guide* .

SSEKMS.description: Specifies the use of server-side encryption using an AWS Key Management Service key (SSE-KMS) to encrypt the delivered S3 Storage Lens metrics export file.

Delimiter.description: This property contains the details of the S3 Storage Lens delimiter being used.

MaxDepth.description: This property contains the details of the max depth that S3 Storage Lens will collect metrics up to.

MinStorageBytesPercentage.description: This property contains the details of the minimum storage bytes percentage threshold that S3 Storage Lens will collect metrics up to.

SelectionCriteria.description: This resource contains the details of the Amazon S3 Storage Lens selection criteria.

AccountLevel.description: This property contains the details of the account-level metrics for Amazon S3 Storage Lens configuration.

AwsOrg.description: This property contains the details of the AWS Organization for the S3 Storage Lens configuration.

DataExport.description: This property contains the details of this S3 Storage Lens configuration's metrics export.

Exclude.description: This property contains the details of the bucket and or Regions excluded for Amazon S3 Storage Lens configuration.

Id.description: This property contains the details of the ID of the S3 Storage Lens configuration.

Include.description: This property contains the details of the bucket and or Regions included for Amazon S3 Storage Lens configuration.

IsEnabled.description: This property contains the details of whether the Amazon S3 Storage Lens configuration is enabled.

PrefixDelimiter.description: The delimiter to divide S3 key into hierarchy of prefixes.

StorageLensArn.description: This property contains the details of the ARN of the S3 Storage Lens configuration. This property is read-only.

StorageLensConfiguration.description: This is the property of the Amazon S3 Storage Lens configuration.

S3BucketDestination.description: S3 bucket destination settings for the Amazon S3 Storage Lens metrics export.

StorageLensTableDestination.description: S3 Tables destination settings for the Amazon S3 Storage Lens metrics export.

StorageLensGroupSelectionCriteria.description: This property indicates which Storage Lens group ARNs to include or exclude in the Storage Lens group aggregation. If this value is left null, then all Storage Lens groups are selected.

StorageLensGroupLevel.description: This resource determines the scope of Storage Lens group data that is displayed in the Storage Lens dashboard.

Exclude.description: This property indicates which Storage Lens group ARNs to exclude from the Storage Lens group aggregation.

Include.description: This property indicates which Storage Lens group ARNs to include in the Storage Lens group aggregation.

StorageLensGroupSelectionCriteria.description: This resource indicates which Storage Lens group ARNs to include or exclude in the Storage Lens group aggregation. You can only attach Storage Lens groups to your dashboard if they're included in your Storage Lens group aggregation. If this value is left null, then all Storage Lens groups are selected.

Encryption.description: Configures the server-side encryption for Amazon S3 Storage Lens report files with either S3-managed keys (SSE-S3) or KMS-managed keys (SSE-KMS).

IsEnabled.description: Specifies whether the export to S3 Tables is enabled or disabled.

StorageLensTableDestination.description: S3 Tables destination settings for the Amazon S3 Storage Lens metrics export.
